President Obama has declared May 3, 2016, as National Teacher Appreciation Day and May 1-7, 2016, as National Teacher Appreciation Week. In a proclamation, the President recognizes the important role that teachers play in shaping our country's future. He emphasizes the need for a diverse group of teachers who can represent the wide range of backgrounds and origins in our society. The President highlights his administration's efforts to support and strengthen the teaching profession, including investments in education and initiatives to recruit and reward talented teachers. He also mentions the bipartisan Every Student Succeeds Act (ESSA), which aims to prepare students for college and careers and reduce the burden of standardized testing. The President calls on students, parents, and all Americans to recognize and appreciate the hard work and dedication of our nation's teachers.